cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of image dehazing and its impact on image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of deep learning models for image classification, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of objective metrics for evaluating image dehazing, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of synthetic and real datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), respectively.
